- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of machine learning techniques to identify implicit discourse relations in open-domain dialogue systems is a key aspect of this paper, making it relevant to the AI community. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel pipeline for identifying discourse relations in open-domain dialogue systems, which involves the use of machine learning models. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The identification of discourse relations in open-domain dialogue systems can be seen as a form of information retrieval, as it involves extracting relevant information from a large corpus of dialogic turns. 
- cs.SD (Sound): This category is less likely, but it is possible that the paper could be relevant to the study of sound in dialogue systems, as the identification of discourse relations could potentially improve the quality of spoken dialogue systems.
